    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-04T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-04T13:00:00-05:00" n="668"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d668">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">638.5131/57: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-04T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 4, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. My telegram No. 42, May 29, 1 p.m.<note n="41" xml:id="d668fn41">Not
                        printed.</note> On instructions of Haitian Government, Fiscal Representative
                    today informed customhouses that French imports no longer come under
                    most-favored-nation treatment and will be subject to maximum tariff, that is,
                    100 per cent surcharge on former regular tariff.</p>
                <p>Goods on high seas as of May 27 exempted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chapin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
